python main.py -d /path/to/files

python main.py -d /path/to/cutouts_xxxx_xxxx_15s/xxxx -c /path/to/results.csv

Second last directory always needs to end in _xxs, as this will be extracted and used as the timescale. Example and modified code specific for working
with TRON outputs. Otherwise just use -t to override timescale.

For example:

python main.py -d /path/to/cutouts_1572120061_LMC1R12C08_8s/eta_V_MAD_high -c /path/to/results.csv

To see options:
python main.py -h 
